<ul class="panelbar">
    <li class="k-state-active">
        <span class="k-link k-state-selected">Question @Model?.Id</span>
        <div>
            <p>
                @Html.Raw(Model.H1OpenTag)
                Northern Trail Outfitters' European and Asia Pacific sales teams have different business requirements on how to create new opportunities.
                @Html.Raw(Model.H1CloseTag)
            </p>
            <p>
                @Html.Raw(Model.H2OpenTag)
                The teams must configure a set of geographically-specific fields relevant only to their team as well as common fields that both teams will utilize. 
                @Html.Raw(Model.H2CloseTag)
            </p>           
            <p>
                Additionally, each team should NOT be able to report on the other's region-specific fields.
            </p>
            <p>
                What solution should be recommended?
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li class="k-state-active">
        Answers
        <div>
            <p>
                <ul class="fieldlist">
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Utilize Visualforce to build an opportunity page that dynamically checks the user's region to determine which fields to display.
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Build a custom object with private sharing to capture the additional fields as a separate record.
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Implement field-level security to allow access to fields for the respective regional sales teams.
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Create separate page layouts and record types for each of the regional sales teams.
                        </label>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
</ul>